\begin_layout Section*
Error Analysis Cheat Sheet
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sec:Cheat-Sheet"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote

\emph on
A MEASUREMENT WITHOUT ERROR BARS IS MEANINGLESS!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Error
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

analysis means quantifying the uncertainty in a measurement/prediction,
 
\emph on
not
\emph default
 comparing a measurement to a previously accepted value.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace smallskip
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $x\pm\Delta x$
\end_inset

 means that the true value of 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 is likely to lie between 
\begin_inset Formula $x-\Delta x$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $x+\Delta x$
\end_inset

 (c.f.
 Section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:Advanced-Topics"

\end_inset

 for what precisely 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

likely
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 means).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace smallskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Systematic
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

error: repeatable but unaccounted for errors, i.e.
 environmental conditions, improper calibration, etc.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Random
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

(statistical)
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

error: unpredictable and uncontrollable influences on the experiment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Accuracy: tendency for 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 repeated measurements to average to the true value as 
\begin_inset Formula $N\to\infty$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Precision: tendency for repeated measurements to all be near the same value
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Absolute
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

error: the 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta x$
\end_inset

 in 
\begin_inset Formula $x\pm\Delta x$
\end_inset

, always has the same units as 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Relative
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

error: 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta x/x$
\end_inset

 quoted as a percentage (
\begin_inset Formula $x\pm\left(100\times\frac{\Delta x}{x}\right)\%$
\end_inset

)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace smallskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
General lab advice: your systematic errors are probably more important than
 your random errors, and probably larger than you think.
 Work hard on your systematics.
 Try to understand the physics of the lab as much as possible, especially
 how and why things could go wrong.
 Get your hands dirty.
 And have fun!
\begin_inset VSpace smallskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
General linear error propagation formula (c.f.
 Section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sub:Linear-Error-Propagation"

\end_inset

):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\Delta f\left(x_{0},y_{0},z_{0},\cdots\right)=\left|\frac{\partial f}{\partial x}\right|_{x=x_{0},\cdots}\Delta x+\left|\frac{\partial f}{\partial y}\right|_{x=x_{0},\cdots}\Delta y+\left|\frac{\partial f}{\partial z}\right|_{x=x_{0},\cdots}\Delta z+\cdots
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Derived formulas:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\Delta\left(x+y+z+\cdots\right) & =\Delta x+\Delta y+\Delta z+\cdots\\
\Delta\left(cx\right) & =\left|c\right|\Delta x,\ c=\mathrm{known\ constant}\\
\frac{\Delta\left(xyz\right)}{\left|xyz\right|} & =\frac{\Delta x}{\left|x\right|}+\frac{\Delta y}{\left|y\right|}+\frac{\Delta z}{\left|z\right|}\\
\frac{\Delta\left(x^{n}\right)}{\left|x^{n}\right|} & =\left|n\frac{\Delta x}{x}\right|\\
\frac{\Delta\left(x/y\right)}{\left|x/y\right|} & =\frac{\Delta x}{\left|x\right|}+\frac{\Delta y}{\left|y\right|}
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Averaging 
\begin_inset Formula $N\ge5$
\end_inset

 independent repeated measurements 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{i}$
\end_inset

 with equal errors 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta x$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\bar{x}\pm\Delta\bar{x}=\left(\sum_{i=1}^{N}\frac{x_{i}}{N}\right)\pm\frac{\Delta x}{\sqrt{N}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace smallskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\emph on
DO NOT ROUND INTERMEDIATE RESULTS!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Round errors 
\emph on
up
\emph default
 to two significant digits (e.g.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\pm28.1$
\end_inset

 rounds up to 
\begin_inset Formula $ $
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\pm29$
\end_inset

).
 Round central values to a precision commensurate with the error, using
 standard rounding (
\begin_inset Formula $.5$
\end_inset

 to 
\begin_inset Formula $1$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $.49$
\end_inset

 to 
\begin_inset Formula $0$
\end_inset

).
 Thus 
\begin_inset Formula $123.45678901\pm0.00234567\to123.4568\pm0.0024$
\end_inset

.
 Equivalent ways to quote this value are 
\begin_inset Formula $123.4568\left(24\right)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $123.4568\pm0.002\%$
\end_inset

.
 (c.f.
 Section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sub:Absolute-and-Relative-Errors"

\end_inset

 for discussion of rounding & quoting errors)
\end_layout

